19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 51.1b of Title 74, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Targeted
23 Violence Prevention Act”.
24
Req. No. 1752 Page 1

1 B. The Office of Homeland Security is authorized to collect,
2 analyze, and disseminate information concerning the activity and
3 identity of individuals that, with probable cause, are suspected of
4 involvement in terrorism, targeted violence, threats to public
5 safety, or any other threats of organized or violent crime to law
6 enforcement and public safety agencies.
7 C. Any information disseminated pursuant to the provisions of
8 this section shall be confidential, and the recipients of such
9 information shall comply with the handling terms associated with the
10 disclosure. Unauthorized release or unauthorized use of information
11 disseminated pursuant to this section shall be a felony punishable
12 by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for
13 a term not to exceed three (3) years, by a fine not more than Fifty
14 Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00), or by both such imprisonment and
15 fine. Such offense shall also be punishable by termination of
16 employment and revocation of the individual’s certification as a
17 peace officer in this state. As used in this subsection,
18 “unauthorized release” or “unauthorized use” shall include, but not
19 be limited to, disseminating or disclosing confidential information
20 in a manner which exceeds the scope of the handling terms associated
21 with the disclosure or is in violation of any rules promulgated
22 pursuant to this act. Provided, however, the following shall not
23 constitute an unauthorized release or unauthorized use of
24 confidential information disseminated by the Office:
Req. No. 1752 Page 2

1 1. Sharing the confidential information with a law enforcement
2 officer or prosecutorial authority for use in a criminal
3 investigation or prosecution; or
4 2. Sharing the confidential information with the express
5 authority of the Homeland Security Advisor or the Advisor’s
6 designee.
7 D. Information collected or disseminated pursuant to the
8 provisions of this section shall be privileged and not discoverable
9 nor subject to subpoena or order for production issued by any court,
10 other than production in a district court criminal proceeding for
11 the prosecution of crimes which are the subject of the information
12 sought.
13 E. The Commissioner of Public Safety is authorized to
14 promulgate rules to effectuate the provisions of this section.
